rca of the issue:
The CRA dev runtime error overlay (react-error-overlay) intercepts ANY window 'error' event including the harmless 'ResizeObserver loop completed with undelivered notifications' that Radix UI's Select+Dialog combo triggers when the popper measures content. Once shown, the overlay renders as a top-level fixed iframe over the whole document, blocking all pointer events to underlying UI. Reproduction: open Dashboard -> click knob-1 -> open action-type Select. Mitigation: in /app/frontend/src/index.js add
  window.addEventListener('error', (e) => { if (e.message && e.message.includes('ResizeObserver')) { e.stopImmediatePropagation(); e.preventDefault(); } });
or build/serve in production mode.
